2026-03-29T13:35:46.3710207Z               "id": "dfe3627c16d870eb86f28b65f8e21c5e3e811b4b",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3711670Z               "message": "Fix early return in LoadBatteryStatusAsync skipping connectivity query\n\nThe method returned early when no battery-type devices existed in the DB,\nwhich also skipped the unreachable device connectivity query below it.\nWrap battery processing in a conditional block instead so connectivity\nis always checked.\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01N2A7MASDjYVWA5SWYBa7rP",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3713068Z               "timestamp": "2026-03-29T11:40:37Z",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3713377Z               "tree_id": "c9e2fc54d341fd8e2f2b5a6a02cdf28cc97c3513",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3713880Z               "url": "https://github.com/***/hpoll/commit/dfe3627c16d870eb86f28b65f8e21c5e3e811b4b"
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3714271Z             },
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3714445Z             {
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3714614Z               "author": {
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3715290Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3715566Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3715796Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3716021Z               },
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3716209Z               "committer": {
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3716439Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3716697Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3716924Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3717142Z               },
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3717328Z               "distinct": false,
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3717602Z               "id": "f15fe6fbc5ad85c037447ab944384fbd3e9b4dac",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3719663Z               "message": "Fix battery and connectivity not showing on admin detail page\n\nGetOrCreateDeviceAsync stores one device per HueDeviceId (the physical\ndevice), so the DeviceType reflects whichever resource was polled first\n(typically motion). Querying by DeviceType == Battery found nothing.\n\nFix: query DeviceReadings by ReadingType instead of filtering Devices by\nDeviceType. This matches how EmailRenderer already queries the data.\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01N2A7MASDjYVWA5SWYBa7rP",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3721638Z               "timestamp": "2026-03-29T11:45:30Z",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3722183Z               "tree_id": "91db4a0168faf0d8822d606d859006a264af0d97",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3723080Z               "url": "https://github.com/***/hpoll/commit/f15fe6fbc5ad85c037447ab944384fbd3e9b4dac"
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3723769Z             },
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3724086Z             {
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3724407Z               "author": {
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3725084Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3725534Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3725913Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3726291Z               },
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3726581Z               "committer": {
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3726823Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3727093Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3727335Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3727733Z               },
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3727924Z               "distinct": false,
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3728208Z               "id": "97459c7d94a9f7b1ba375eab62c26adb4b778dba",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3730958Z               "message": "Fix device types: use physical archetype instead of per-service types\n\nPreviously, each Hue service endpoint (motion, temperature, battery,\nconnectivity) created separate Device rows with service-specific types.\nA single physical motion sensor would get DeviceType \"motion_sensor\",\n\"battery\", or \"zigbee_connectivity\" depending on which service created\nit first. Stale device removal was also per-type, missing cross-type\ndevices.\n\nNow: one Device row per physical Hue device, with DeviceType set from\nthe Hue device archetype (e.g. \"motion_sensor\"). All reading types\n(motion, temperature, battery, connectivity) attach to the same device.\nStale removal is a single pass across all service types.\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01Gmjk912cuixJo7D9UqZQGA",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3733639Z               "timestamp": "2026-03-29T12:05:17Z",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3733954Z               "tree_id": "a23e7285e29a338abd854160c68b95b7eea24bc5",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3734467Z               "url": "https://github.com/***/hpoll/commit/97459c7d94a9f7b1ba375eab62c26adb4b778dba"
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3735148Z             },
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3735324Z             {
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3735504Z               "author": {
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3735735Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3736018Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3736241Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3736461Z               },
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3736642Z               "committer": {
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3736873Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3737134Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3737355Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3737577Z               },
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3737766Z               "distinct": false,
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3738038Z               "id": "b37163e189963ac8a6e625b4c1680c52a19941d7",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3741757Z               "message": "Derive device type from Hue services array, not metadata archetype\n\nThe Hue API metadata.archetype field only covers lighting form factors\n(e.g. \"classic_bulb\", \"spot_bulb\") and returns \"unknown_archetype\" for\nsensors. Using it as DeviceType would break queries that filter by\n\"motion_sensor\".\n\nInstead, derive the device type from the device's services[] array:\nif it has an rtype \"motion\" service → motion_sensor, \"temperature\" →\ntemperature_sensor, otherwise → unknown. This correctly identifies\nphysical motion sensors regardless of their Hue archetype.\n\nUpdated test mock devices to use realistic \"unknown_archetype\" values\n(matching what real Hue motion sensors report) to verify the\nservices-based derivation works correctly.\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01Gmjk912cuixJo7D9UqZQGA",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3744554Z               "timestamp": "2026-03-29T12:10:39Z",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3745148Z               "tree_id": "3999893010f4273ad83bc2baaf250e12df118034",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3745732Z               "url": "https://github.com/***/hpoll/commit/b37163e189963ac8a6e625b4c1680c52a19941d7"
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3746124Z             },
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3746294Z             {
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3746474Z               "author": {
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3746708Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3746970Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3747206Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3747429Z               },
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3747644Z               "committer": {
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3747880Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3748141Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3748383Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3748613Z               },
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3748949Z               "distinct": false,
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3749222Z               "id": "b1cc937d44d921b69aebbddf9c9919c16b642d15",
2026-03-29T13:35:46.3750927Z               "message": "Only run stale device removal when all endpoints are polled\n\nOn non-battery poll cycles, only motion and temperature endpoints are\nqueried. Devices that only appear in battery/connectivity (lights,\nplugs, switches) would not be in allCurrentDeviceIds and would be\nincorrectly removed as stale. Now stale removal only runs when\nshouldPollBattery is true, ensuring we have the complete picture.\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01Gmjk912cuixJo7D9UqZQGA",
